  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior/ Manager, Digital Health Readiness (2-years Contract)",
  "description": "<p>As SingHealth prepares for the implementation of the Next Generation Electronic Medical Record (NGEMR) system, our Digital Health Readiness (DHR) team plays a pivotal role in shaping the future of healthcare delivery. As a Senior Manager, you will drive comprehensive digital readiness and change management programmes across our healthcare cluster, spanning clinical, operational, and administrative domains.</p><p><br /></p><p>Your responsibilities include:</p><ul><li>Design and implement DHR strategies to support organisational transformation, including digital initiatives, restructures, or cultural shifts</li><li>Lead workshops, focus groups, and surveys to gauge employee sentiment and readiness</li><li>Oversee the design and delivery of training programmes to ensure employees are equipped for new systems, tools, or processes</li><li>Conduct impact assessments to identify potential risks and areas of resistance</li><li>Develop and execute comprehensive communication plans to articulate the rationale, benefits, and progress of DHR initiatives</li><li>Identify, analyse, and engage key stakeholders across all levels of the organisation</li><li>Support senior leaders and executives in fulfilling their DHR roles</li><li>Monitor and manage risks associated with DHR efforts, providing contingency plans as needed</li><li>Conduct post-implementation evaluations and lessons learnt reviews</li></ul><p>Job Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Behavioural Science, Human Factors or Communications or equivalent with minimum 6 years of relevant experience</li><li>Experience in healthcare settings with knowledge of hospital operations (clinical and/or support functions) will be advantageous</li><li>Experience in Organisational Development will be an advantage</li><li>Professional certification in Change Management (e.g., PROSCI, CCMP) will be an advantage</li><li>Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills</li><li>Task driven, strong facilitation, planning and analytical skills</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 6,
